by xabbuh at 2018-09-27T12:23:42Z

I think there's a misunderstanding here. `serializer` is indeed the directory you can use in your application, but in a bundle the directory which is looked for is still serialization (see https://github.com/symfony/symfony/blob/60fac5cefaea25e2b56c1bad7a8a3807fff6d00f/src/Symfony/Bundle/FrameworkBundle/DependencyInjection/FrameworkExtension.php#L1334-L1336).

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by robob4him at 2018-09-30T17:14:02Z

A misunderstanding to an extent, perhaps, but "can" is overstated. Symfony 4 does not look for "serialization" in the config directory. Whether that's "flex" or "bundle" or whatnot it needs to be added. Three hours of research proves that to me. I welcome whatever suggestions you have.

