by xabbuh at 2018-10-01T09:43:03Z

I think we are talking about different things. When you are talking about the `serialization` directory in the `config` directory, that's right. But in this case we are not in a bundle context.

I think what will probably be the solution here is to expand this list to mention the locations where you would store the files on the application level. So the final list will look something like this:

```rst
* All ``*.yaml`` and ``*.xml`` files in the ``config/serializer/``
  directory.
* The ``serialization.yaml`` or ``serialization.xml`` file in
  the ``Resources/config/`` directory of a bundle;
* All ``*.yaml`` and ``*.xml`` files in the ``Resources/config/serialization/``
  directory of a bundle.
```

Does that make sense?

